title: Fixed a few unrelated bugs
message:
Fixed a few unrelated bugs

There was a problem linking to DTables where it didn't give all
arguments needed. Picasso has problems with gifs for some reason, so for
now I check for gifs and don't load them. Hopefully this can be changed.
Also changed the linking scheme slightly. DTables no longer do special
sting escaping/formatting for making links. It was too confusing when
working with iOS, so we want to stay as close to the original titles as
possible.

title: Add hashCode to prediction
message:
Add hashCode to prediction

Prediction had a hard coded equals method and ignored the lombok generated one because it ignored the minutes field. Lombok actually has an option for @EqualsAndHashCode called exclude that will do this for us. We get an equals and hashCode method for free. Fixes T159.

is a new wrapper around the floating action button making it easier to
use.

Fixes T152

title: Linking Synchronously
message:
Linking Synchronously

Summary:
Illustrate problems with linking

Sometimes we need to go to the internet to link. Sometimes we don't.
I've separated out the channels into those that need internet and those
that don't. This is not meant as a long term solution. We need to figure
out what to do with DTables, readers, and SoC to get them to not need
internet to link.

be consistently using.

title: Don't load credits and open sections in SoC search
message:
Don't load credits and open sections in SoC search

We need to open a new HTTP connection for each Course every time we get
credits and open sections. This causes incredible slowdown, so instead
we've opted to not show it at all. The data is now loaded when a course
is clicked.
